PrecisRegulations Amending the ONTARIO FISHERY REGULATIONS, 1989 - which, in the interests of sound resource management, impose new bait and ice-fishing restrictions, allow live leeches to be imported, bait fish to be taken for personal use and commercially purchased fish to be used in privately-owned ponds, and adjust yellow perch and lake specific quotas, fishing line length limits and close times.
